-{"id":"bd-bacf","title":"Fix frontend silent mock data fallback hiding real errors","description":"# Bug: Frontend Silently Falls Back to Mock Data, Hiding Real Errors

## Problem Statement
Multiple frontend hooks silently replace API errors with mock data. Users see "data" that looks real but is actually fake, with no indication that the real API failed.

## Affected Files
All hooks in `apps/web/src/hooks/` that fetch data:
- `useSnapshot.ts` (lines 275-284)
- `useDCG.ts`
- `useFleet.ts`
- `useCAAM.ts`
- `useNotifications.ts`
- `useDashboard.ts`
- (and others)

## Current Behavior (BROKEN)
```typescript
// useSnapshot.ts pattern seen across all hooks
try {
  const result = await fetchAPI<SystemSnapshot>("/snapshot", bypassCache);
  setData(result);
} catch (e) {
  setError(e instanceof Error ? e : new Error("Unknown error"));
  // Fall back to mock data on error - USER NEVER KNOWS!
  setData(mockSnapshot);
}
```

## Impact
- **User confusion**: Dashboard shows data but nothing works
- **Debugging difficulty**: Errors are hidden, hard to diagnose
- **False confidence**: Operators think system is healthy when it's not
- **Data integrity**: Users may take actions based on fake data

## Root Cause
Development convenience (mock data for offline dev) was left in production paths without clear indication to users.

## Proposed Solution
Three-tier approach:

### Tier 1: Clear Error Display
Show error to user, don't show mock data in production:
```typescript
const [data, setData] = useState<T | null>(null);
const [error, setError] = useState<Error | null>(null);
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);
const [usingMockData, setUsingMockData] = useState(false);

try {
  const result = await fetchAPI<T>(url);
  setData(result);
  setUsingMockData(false);
} catch (e) {
  setError(e instanceof Error ? e : new Error("Unknown error"));

  if (process.env.NODE_ENV === "development" || mockMode) {
    // Only in dev: fall back to mock
    setData(mockData);
    setUsingMockData(true);
  } else {
    // Production: show error, no mock data
    setData(null);
  }
}

// Return the mock data flag so UI can indicate it
return { data, error, isLoading, usingMockData };
```

### Tier 2: Visual Indicator for Mock Data
When mock data is shown (dev mode), display clear banner:
```tsx
function DataComponent() {
  const { data, error, usingMockData } = useSnapshot();

  return (
    <div>
      {usingMockData && (
        <Banner variant="warning">
          ⚠️ Showing mock data - API unavailable
        </Banner>
      )}
      {error && !usingMockData && (
        <ErrorDisplay error={error} />
      )}
      {data && <DataView data={data} />}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Tier 3: Toast Notifications for Errors
Show toast when API fails:
```typescript
} catch (e) {
  const error = e instanceof Error ? e : new Error("Unknown error");
  setError(error);

  // Show toast so user knows something is wrong
  toast.error(`Failed to load data: ${error.message}`);

  if (isDev) {
    setData(mockData);
  }
}
```

## Implementation Details

### Hook Interface Update
All data hooks should return:
```typescript
interface UseDataResult<T> {
  data: T | null;
  error: Error | null;
  isLoading: boolean;
  usingMockData: boolean;
  refetch: () => Promise<void>;
}
```

### Environment Check
```typescript
const isDevelopment = process.env.NODE_ENV === "development";
const forceMockMode = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_MODE === "true";
const allowMockFallback = isDevelopment || forceMockMode;
```

### Files to Update
1. Create `useMockFallback.ts` utility hook
2. Update all data hooks to use new pattern
3. Create `MockDataBanner` component
4. Add toast integration for errors
5. Update pages to render error/mock states

### Example Refactored Hook
```typescript
export function useSnapshot(options?: SnapshotOptions) {
  const [data, setData] = useState<SystemSnapshot | null>(null);
  const [error, setError] = useState<Error | null>(null);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);
  const [usingMockData, setUsingMockData] = useState(false);
  const { toast } = useToast();

  const fetchSnapshot = useCallback(async () => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    setError(null);

    try {
      const result = await fetchAPI<SystemSnapshot>("/snapshot");
      setData(result);
      setUsingMockData(false);
    } catch (e) {
      const err = e instanceof Error ? e : new Error("Failed to fetch snapshot");
      setError(err);

      if (allowMockFallback) {
        setData(mockSnapshot);
        setUsingMockData(true);
        toast.warning("Using mock data - API unavailable");
      } else {
        setData(null);
        toast.error(`Snapshot failed: ${err.message}`);
      }
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  }, []);

  return { data, error, isLoading, usingMockData, refetch: fetchSnapshot };
}
```

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests
1. Test error sets data to null in production mode
2. Test error uses mock data in development mode
3. Test usingMockData flag is set correctly
4. Test toast is called on error

### Integration Tests
1. Mock API failure, verify error UI shown
2. Verify mock data banner appears in dev mode
3. Verify no mock data in production build

### E2E Tests
1. Build production, fail API, verify error shown (not mock)
2. Dev mode, fail API, verify mock banner shown
3. Verify toast notifications appear

## Considerations
- **Backward compatibility**: Existing components expecting data may need updates
- **Loading states**: Ensure skeleton/loading UI handles null data
- **User experience**: Error messages should be actionable
- **Development workflow**: Mock data still useful for offline development

## Definition of Done
- [ ] useMockFallback utility created
- [ ] All hooks updated with new pattern
- [ ] MockDataBanner component created
- [ ] Toast integration for errors
